Start the vrpn server: "vrpn_server". Make sure the vrpn.cfg file in the
the same location

To check if it is actually working, try "vrpn_print_devices
Wand0@localhost" and try doing something with the Wand button. You should
see some changes on the terminal.

open the ParaView client and in the VR pannel, load the file
"VRPluginState.pvvr" and click start. You may want to tweak this file for
different interactions.

You can read more about it here - https://www.paraview.org/Wiki/Immersive_ParaView#Loading_the_VR_plugin_in_ParaView

That's it! 
